<h2>Solar Incentives in Scottsdale</h2>
<p>Scottsdale homeowners can take advantage of multiple solar incentive programs to reduce installation costs. The federal solar Investment Tax Credit (ITC) provides a 30% tax credit on the total system cost, including equipment and installation, which remains at 30% through 2032 before stepping down. Arizona offers additional state-level incentives, including a 25% state tax credit up to \$1,000 for solar installations. SRP customers may also qualify for demand-based rate plans that can further optimize savings when paired with solar systems. Property tax exemptions in Arizona ensure that the added home value from solar installations won't increase property tax assessments, providing long-term financial benefits beyond the initial installation incentives.</p>

<h2>Best Solar Companies in Scottsdale</h2>
<p>When selecting a solar installer in Scottsdale, prioritize companies with proper Arizona licensing, including ROC (Registrar of Contractors) electrical and general contractor licenses. Look for installers with extensive local experience in Maricopa County who understand SRP's interconnection requirements and local permitting processes. Quality installers should offer comprehensive warranties covering equipment (typically 20-25 years for panels, 10-12 years for inverters) and workmanship (minimum 5-10 years). Verify installer credentials through the North American Board of Certified Energy Practitioners (NABCEP), check Better Business Bureau ratings, and request multiple local references from recent customers. The best Scottsdale solar companies will conduct thorough site assessments, provide detailed system production estimates based on local weather data, and handle all permitting and utility interconnection paperwork on your behalf.</p>

